// Brief sample 3 - a while whose body is a single simple statement (an if),
// plus a trailing update separated by a comma. The comma binds to the while
// body, not to the else branch -- see the "body_seq" grammar rule.
// Expected output:
//   x = 3
//   y = 11
x = 1
y = 0
while x < 3 do if x == 1 then y = 10 else y = y + 1, x = x + 1
